				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Firstly, a HUGE thank you to Seijuro to his fantastic walk-throughs for both the molds and the ronium. I know I would have quit before now without them. <BR>
I would like to confirm that you only need around 200 bone chips to raise faction to high amiable with the Clerics of Underfoot. Both myself and another Paladin of my guild went there with 300 bone chips each and we walked away with many spare chips.<BR>
Another point with the Soil of the Underfoot - it is Lore Item. Do not hand in more then 4 fairy dusts at once. I did this without checking and wasted 4 fairy dusts. I believe it is easier to gather all the other items for Ronium first and then go to Kaladim to make the Ronium. As you use each soil of the underfoot, you can replace it with more fairy dust that you have in the bank.<BR>
<BR>
Now I must go and get my MM granite (easily the hardest part of the quest).<BR>
<BR>
Regards<BR>
